--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 The History of The Irda<br>
<br>
&quot; In the ancient days before they grew self centered and seduced by evil, the most beautiful of all races ever created by the gods was the Ogre.&quot; * (Dragonlance, Love and War, tales Vol. 3, p. 314)<br>
<br>
It was in the age when the Ogre were known as the Irda, the chosen of the gods. Made in the image of the gods, the Irda were the masters of the land. Each Irda was beautiful, and blessed with magical powers that neared a god-like awe from the other races of Norrath. As a result of this, the Irda had turned their backs upon the rest of the world, and all of its inhabitants. the gods seeing their creations compare themselves to gods, had grown angry with the Irda. It was decided by the gods, that all the Irda held dear would be taken from them, their beauty, their magic, and their special relationship they shared witht he gods. the Irda were blighted with mishapen forms, gone were the tall, fine boned forms they held so dear, to be replaced by a hideous husk that would serve as a constant reminder of all they had taken for granted. * (The Irda were even more beautiful than the finest of the high elves, their beauty drew races from what was normally considered beautiful by their race. i.e., a dwarven male would find whiskers amongst their women attractive, however that would still not matter, as the Irda were godlike in their form.) No longer were they looked upon as the chosen ones, now they were scorned by all other races, they had become Ogres. (The ogre form in general is very offensive to other races, thus they were spurned.)<br>
